54static Node* previousLeafWithSameEditability(Node* node, EditableType editableType)
55{
56 bool editable = hasEditableStyle(*node, editableType);
57 node = previousLeafNode(node);
58 while (node) {
59 if (editable == hasEditableStyle(*node, editableType))
60 return node;
61 node = previousLeafNode(node);
62 }
63 return nullptr;
64}
65
66static Node* nextLeafWithSameEditability(Node* node, EditableType editableType)
67{
68 if (!node)
69 return nullptr;
70
71 bool editable = hasEditableStyle(*node, editableType);
72 node = nextLeafNode(node);
73 while (node) {
74 if (editable == hasEditableStyle(*node, editableType))
75 return node;
76 node = nextLeafNode(node);
77 }
78 return nullptr;
79}

81// FIXME: consolidate with code in previousLinePosition.
82static Position previousLineCandidatePosition(Node* node, const VisiblePosition& visiblePosition, EditableType editableType)
83{
84 auto* highestRoot = highestEditableRoot(visiblePosition.deepEquivalent(), editableType);
85 Node* previousNode = previousLeafWithSameEditability(node, editableType);
86
87 while (previousNode && (!previousNode->renderer() || inSameLine(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(previousNode), visiblePosition)))
88 previousNode = previousLeafWithSameEditability(previousNode, editableType);
89
90 while (previousNode && !previousNode->isShadowRoot()) {
91 if (highestEditableRoot(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(previousNode), editableType) != highestRoot)
92 break;
93
94 Position pos = previousNode->hasTagName(brTag) ? positionBeforeNode(previousNode) :
95 makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(previousNode, caretMaxOffset(*previousNode));
96
97 if (pos.isCandidate())
98 return pos;
99
100 previousNode = previousLeafWithSameEditability(previousNode, editableType);
101 }
102 return Position();
103}
104
105static Position nextLineCandidatePosition(Node* node, const VisiblePosition& visiblePosition, EditableType editableType)
106{
107 auto* highestRoot = highestEditableRoot(visiblePosition.deepEquivalent(), editableType);
108 Node* nextNode = nextLeafWithSameEditability(node, editableType);
109 while (nextNode && (!nextNode->renderer() || inSameLine(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(nextNode), visiblePosition)))
110 nextNode = nextLeafWithSameEditability(nextNode, ContentIsEditable);
111
112 while (nextNode && !nextNode->isShadowRoot()) {
113 if (highestEditableRoot(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(nextNode), editableType) != highestRoot)
114 break;
115
116 Position pos;
117 pos = makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(nextNode, caretMinOffset(*nextNode));
118
119 if (pos.isCandidate())
120 return pos;
121
122 nextNode = nextLeafWithSameEditability(nextNode, editableType);
123 }
124 return Position();
125}

127static bool isTextOrLineBreakRun(LayoutIntegration::RunIterator run)
128{
129 return run && (run->isText() || run->renderer().isBR());
130}
131
132static LayoutIntegration::RunIterator previousTextOrLineBreakRun(LayoutIntegration::RunIterator run)
133{
134 while (run) {
135 run.traversePreviousOnLineInLogicalOrder();
136 if (isTextOrLineBreakRun(run))
137 return run;
138 }
139 return { };
140}
141
142static LayoutIntegration::RunIterator nextTextOrLineBreakRun(LayoutIntegration::RunIterator run)
143{
144 while (run) {
145 run.traverseNextOnLineInLogicalOrder();
146 if (isTextOrLineBreakRun(run))
147 return run;
148 }
149 return { };
150}
151
152static LayoutIntegration::RunIterator startTextOrLineBreakRun(LayoutIntegration::LineIterator line)
153{
154 auto run = line.logicalStartRun();
155 if (isTextOrLineBreakRun(run))
156 return run;
157 return nextTextOrLineBreakRun(run);
158}
159
160static LayoutIntegration::RunIterator endTextOrLineBreakRun(LayoutIntegration::LineIterator line)
161{
162 auto run = line.logicalEndRun();
163 if (isTextOrLineBreakRun(run))
164 return run;
165 return previousTextOrLineBreakRun(run);
166}

168static const LayoutIntegration::RunIterator logicallyPreviousRun(const VisiblePosition& visiblePosition, LayoutIntegration::RunIterator startRun, bool& previousBoxInDifferentLine)
169{
170 if (auto previousRun = previousTextOrLineBreakRun(startRun))
171 return previousRun;
172
173 if (auto previousLine = startRun.line().previous()) {
174 // FIXME: Why isn't previousBoxInDifferentLine set here?
175 if (auto previousRun = endTextOrLineBreakRun(previousLine))
176 return previousRun;
177 }
178
179 while (1) {
180 auto* startNode = startRun->renderer().nonPseudoNode();
181 if (!startNode)
182 break;
183
184 Position position = previousLineCandidatePosition(startNode, visiblePosition, ContentIsEditable);
185 if (position.isNull())
186 break;
187
188 RenderedPosition renderedPosition(position, Affinity::Downstream);
189 auto previousLine = renderedPosition.line();
190 if (!previousLine)
191 break;
192
193 if (previousLine != startRun.line()) {
194 if (auto previousRun = endTextOrLineBreakRun(previousLine)) {
195 previousBoxInDifferentLine = true;
196 return previousRun;
197 }
198 }
199
200 startRun = previousLine.logicalStartRun();
201 }
202 return { };
203}
204
205
206static const LayoutIntegration::RunIterator logicallyNextRun(const VisiblePosition& visiblePosition, LayoutIntegration::RunIterator startRun, bool& nextBoxInDifferentLine)
207{
208 if (auto nextRun = nextTextOrLineBreakRun(startRun))
209 return nextRun;
210
211 if (auto nextLine = startRun.line().next()) {
212 // FIXME: Why isn't previousBoxInDifferentLine set here?
213 if (auto nextRun = startTextOrLineBreakRun(nextLine))
214 return nextRun;
215 }
216
217 while (1) {
218 auto* startNode = startRun->renderer().nonPseudoNode();
219 if (!startNode)
220 break;
221
222 Position position = nextLineCandidatePosition(startNode, visiblePosition, ContentIsEditable);
223 if (position.isNull())
224 break;
225
226 RenderedPosition renderedPosition(position, Affinity::Downstream);
227 auto nextLine = renderedPosition.line();
228 if (!nextLine)
229 break;
230
231 if (nextLine != startRun.line()) {
232 if (auto nextRun = startTextOrLineBreakRun(nextLine)) {
233 nextBoxInDifferentLine = true;
234 return nextRun;
235 }
236 }
237
238 startRun = nextLine.logicalEndRun();
239 }
240 return { };
241}

243static UBreakIterator* wordBreakIteratorForMinOffsetBoundary(const VisiblePosition& visiblePosition, LayoutIntegration::TextRunIterator textRun,
244 unsigned& previousRunLength, bool& previousRunInDifferentLine, Vector<UChar, 1024>& string)
245{
246 previousRunInDifferentLine = false;
247
248 auto previousRun = logicallyPreviousRun(visiblePosition, textRun, previousRunInDifferentLine);
249 while (previousRun && !previousRun->isText()) {
250 ASSERT(previousRun->renderer().isBR());
251 previousRunInDifferentLine = true;
252 previousRun = logicallyPreviousRun(visiblePosition, previousRun, previousRunInDifferentLine);
253 }
254
255 string.clear();
256
257 if (previousRun) {
258 auto& previousTextRun = downcast<LayoutIntegration::TextRunIterator>(previousRun);
259 previousRunLength = previousTextRun->length();
260 append(string, previousTextRun->text());
261 }
262 append(string, textRun->text());
263
264 return wordBreakIterator(StringView(string.data(), string.size()));
265}
266
267static UBreakIterator* wordBreakIteratorForMaxOffsetBoundary(const VisiblePosition& visiblePosition, LayoutIntegration::TextRunIterator textRun,
268 bool& nextRunInDifferentLine, Vector<UChar, 1024>& string)
269{
270 nextRunInDifferentLine = false;
271
272 auto nextRun = logicallyNextRun(visiblePosition, textRun, nextRunInDifferentLine);
273 while (nextRun && !nextRun->isText()) {
274 ASSERT(nextRun->renderer().isBR());
275 nextRunInDifferentLine = true;
276 nextRun = logicallyNextRun(visiblePosition, nextRun, nextRunInDifferentLine);
277 }
278
279 string.clear();
280 append(string, textRun->text());
281
282 if (nextRun) {
283 auto& nextTextRun = downcast<LayoutIntegration::TextRunIterator>(nextRun);
284 append(string, nextTextRun->text());
285 }
286
287 return wordBreakIterator(StringView(string.data(), string.size()));
288}
289
290static bool isLogicalStartOfWord(UBreakIterator* iter, int position, bool hardLineBreak)
291{
292 bool boundary = hardLineBreak ? true : ubrk_isBoundary(iter, position);
293 if (!boundary)
294 return false;
295
296 ubrk_following(iter, position);
297 // isWordTextBreak returns true after moving across a word and false after moving across a punctuation/space.
298 return isWordTextBreak(iter);
299}
300
301static bool islogicalEndOfWord(UBreakIterator* iter, int position, bool hardLineBreak)
302{
303 bool boundary = ubrk_isBoundary(iter, position);
304 return (hardLineBreak || boundary) && isWordTextBreak(iter);
305}
306
307enum CursorMovementDirection { MoveLeft, MoveRight };
308
309static VisiblePosition visualWordPosition(const VisiblePosition& visiblePosition, CursorMovementDirection direction,
310 bool skipsSpaceWhenMovingRight)
311{
312 if (visiblePosition.isNull())
313 return VisiblePosition();
314
315 TextDirection blockDirection = directionOfEnclosingBlock(visiblePosition.deepEquivalent());
316 LayoutIntegration::RunIterator previouslyVisitedRun;
317 VisiblePosition current = visiblePosition;
318 std::optional<VisiblePosition> previousPosition;
319 UBreakIterator* iter = nullptr;
320
321 Vector<UChar, 1024> string;
322
323 while (1) {
324 VisiblePosition adjacentCharacterPosition = direction == MoveRight ? current.right(true) : current.left(true);
325 if (adjacentCharacterPosition == current || adjacentCharacterPosition.isNull())
326 return VisiblePosition();
327 // FIXME: This is a workaround for webkit.org/b/167138.
328 if (previousPosition && adjacentCharacterPosition == previousPosition.value())
329 return VisiblePosition();
330
331 // FIXME: Why force the use of upstream affinity here instead of VisiblePosition::inlineRunAndOffset, which will get affinity from adjacentCharacterPosition?
332 auto [run, offsetInRun] = adjacentCharacterPosition.deepEquivalent().inlineRunAndOffset(Affinity::Upstream);
333
334 if (!run)
335 break;
336 if (!run->isText()) {
337 current = adjacentCharacterPosition;
338 continue;
339 }
340
341 auto& textRun = downcast<LayoutIntegration::TextRunIterator>(run);
342 unsigned previousRunLength = 0;
343 bool previousRunInDifferentLine = false;
344 bool nextRunInDifferentLine = false;
345 bool movingIntoNewRun = previouslyVisitedRun != run;
346
347 if (offsetInRun == textRun->minimumCaretOffset())
348 iter = wordBreakIteratorForMinOffsetBoundary(adjacentCharacterPosition, textRun, previousRunLength, previousRunInDifferentLine, string);
349 else if (offsetInRun == textRun->maximumCaretOffset())
350 iter = wordBreakIteratorForMaxOffsetBoundary(adjacentCharacterPosition, textRun, nextRunInDifferentLine, string);
351 else if (movingIntoNewRun) {
352 iter = wordBreakIterator(textRun->text());
353 previouslyVisitedRun = run;
354 }
355
356 if (!iter)
357 break;
358
359 ubrk_first(iter);
360 int offsetInIterator = offsetInRun - textRun->start() + previousRunLength;
361
362 bool isWordBreak;
363 bool boxHasSameDirectionalityAsBlock = run->direction() == blockDirection;
364 bool movingBackward = (direction == MoveLeft && run->direction() == TextDirection::LTR) || (direction == MoveRight && run->direction() == TextDirection::RTL);
365 if ((skipsSpaceWhenMovingRight && boxHasSameDirectionalityAsBlock)
366 || (!skipsSpaceWhenMovingRight && movingBackward)) {
367 bool logicalStartInRenderer = offsetInRun == textRun->start() && previousRunInDifferentLine;
368 isWordBreak = isLogicalStartOfWord(iter, offsetInIterator, logicalStartInRenderer);
369 if (isWordBreak && offsetInRun == run->maximumCaretOffset() && nextRunInDifferentLine)
370 isWordBreak = false;
371 } else {
372 bool logicalEndInRenderer = offsetInRun == textRun->end() && nextRunInDifferentLine;
373 isWordBreak = islogicalEndOfWord(iter, offsetInIterator, logicalEndInRenderer);
374 if (isWordBreak && offsetInRun == run->minimumCaretOffset() && previousRunInDifferentLine)
375 isWordBreak = false;
376 }
377
378 if (isWordBreak)
379 return adjacentCharacterPosition;
380
381 previousPosition = current;
382 current = adjacentCharacterPosition;
383 }
384 return VisiblePosition();
385}
386
387VisiblePosition leftWordPosition(const VisiblePosition& visiblePosition, bool skipsSpaceWhenMovingRight)
388{
389 VisiblePosition leftWordBreak = visualWordPosition(visiblePosition, MoveLeft, skipsSpaceWhenMovingRight);
390 leftWordBreak = visiblePosition.honorEditingBoundaryAtOrBefore(leftWordBreak);
391
392 // FIXME: How should we handle a non-editable position?
393 if (leftWordBreak.isNull() && isEditablePosition(visiblePosition.deepEquivalent())) {
394 TextDirection blockDirection = directionOfEnclosingBlock(visiblePosition.deepEquivalent());
395 leftWordBreak = blockDirection == TextDirection::LTR ? startOfEditableContent(visiblePosition) : endOfEditableContent(visiblePosition);
396 }
397 return leftWordBreak;
398}
399
400VisiblePosition rightWordPosition(const VisiblePosition& visiblePosition, bool skipsSpaceWhenMovingRight)
401{
402 VisiblePosition rightWordBreak = visualWordPosition(visiblePosition, MoveRight, skipsSpaceWhenMovingRight);
403 rightWordBreak = visiblePosition.honorEditingBoundaryAtOrBefore(rightWordBreak);
404
405 // FIXME: How should we handle a non-editable position?
406 if (rightWordBreak.isNull() && isEditablePosition(visiblePosition.deepEquivalent())) {
407 TextDirection blockDirection = directionOfEnclosingBlock(visiblePosition.deepEquivalent());
408 rightWordBreak = blockDirection == TextDirection::LTR ? endOfEditableContent(visiblePosition) : startOfEditableContent(visiblePosition);
409 }
410 return rightWordBreak;
411}

414static void prepend(Vector<UChar, 1024>& buffer, StringView string)
415{
416 unsigned oldSize = buffer.size();
417 unsigned length = string.length();
418 buffer.grow(oldSize + length);
419 memmove(buffer.data() + length, buffer.data(), oldSize * sizeof(UChar));
420 for (unsigned i = 0; i < length; ++i)
421 buffer[i] = string[i];
422}
423
424static void prependRepeatedCharacter(Vector<UChar, 1024>& buffer, UChar character, unsigned count)
425{
426 unsigned oldSize = buffer.size();
427 buffer.grow(oldSize + count);
428 memmove(buffer.data() + count, buffer.data(), oldSize * sizeof(UChar));
429 for (unsigned i = 0; i < count; ++i)
430 buffer[i] = character;
431}
432
433static void appendRepeatedCharacter(Vector<UChar, 1024>& buffer, UChar character, unsigned count)
434{
435 unsigned oldSize = buffer.size();
436 buffer.grow(oldSize + count);
437 for (unsigned i = 0; i < count; ++i)
438 buffer[oldSize + i] = character;
439}

441unsigned suffixLengthForRange(const SimpleRange& forwardsScanRange, Vector<UChar, 1024>& string)
442{
443 unsigned suffixLength = 0;
444 TextIterator forwardsIterator(forwardsScanRange);
445 while (!forwardsIterator.atEnd()) {
446 StringView text = forwardsIterator.text();
447 unsigned i = endOfFirstWordBoundaryContext(text);
448 append(string, text.substring(0, i));
449 suffixLength += i;
450 if (i < text.length())
451 break;
452 forwardsIterator.advance();
453 }
454 return suffixLength;
455}
456
457unsigned prefixLengthForRange(const SimpleRange& backwardsScanRange, Vector<UChar, 1024>& string)
458{
459 unsigned prefixLength = 0;
460 SimplifiedBackwardsTextIterator backwardsIterator(backwardsScanRange);
461 while (!backwardsIterator.atEnd()) {
462 StringView text = backwardsIterator.text();
463 int i = startOfLastWordBoundaryContext(text);
464 prepend(string, text.substring(i));
465 prefixLength += text.length() - i;
466 if (i > 0)
467 break;
468 backwardsIterator.advance();
469 }
470 return prefixLength;
471}
472
473unsigned backwardSearchForBoundaryWithTextIterator(SimplifiedBackwardsTextIterator& it, Vector<UChar, 1024>& string, unsigned suffixLength, BoundarySearchFunction searchFunction)
474{
475 unsigned next = 0;
476 bool needMoreContext = false;
477 while (!it.atEnd()) {
478 bool inTextSecurityMode = it.node() && it.node()->renderer() && it.node()->renderer()->style().textSecurity() != TextSecurity::None;
479 // iterate to get chunks until the searchFunction returns a non-zero value.
480 if (!inTextSecurityMode)
481 prepend(string, it.text());
482 else {
483 // Treat bullets used in the text security mode as regular characters when looking for boundaries
484 prependRepeatedCharacter(string, 'x', it.text().length());
485 }
486 if (string.size() > suffixLength) {
487 next = searchFunction(StringView(string.data(), string.size()), string.size() - suffixLength, MayHaveMoreContext, needMoreContext);
488 if (next > 1) // FIXME: This is a work around for https://webkit.org/b/115070. We need to provide more contexts in general case.
489 break;
490 }
491 it.advance();
492 }
493 if (needMoreContext && string.size() > suffixLength) {
494 // The last search returned the beginning of the buffer and asked for more context,
495 // but there is no earlier text. Force a search with what's available.
496 next = searchFunction(StringView(string.data(), string.size()), string.size() - suffixLength, DontHaveMoreContext, needMoreContext);
497 ASSERT(!needMoreContext);
498 }
499
500 return next;
501}
502
503unsigned forwardSearchForBoundaryWithTextIterator(TextIterator& it, Vector<UChar, 1024>& string, unsigned prefixLength, BoundarySearchFunction searchFunction)
504{
505 unsigned next = 0;
506 bool needMoreContext = false;
507 while (!it.atEnd()) {
508 bool inTextSecurityMode = it.node() && it.node()->renderer() && it.node()->renderer()->style().textSecurity() != TextSecurity::None;
509 // Keep asking the iterator for chunks until the search function
510 // returns an end value not equal to the length of the string passed to it.
511 if (!inTextSecurityMode)
512 append(string, it.text());
513 else {
514 // Treat bullets used in the text security mode as regular characters when looking for boundaries
515 appendRepeatedCharacter(string, 'x', it.text().length());
516 }
517 if (string.size() > prefixLength) {
518 next = searchFunction(StringView(string.data(), string.size()), prefixLength, MayHaveMoreContext, needMoreContext);
519 if (next != string.size())
520 break;
521 }
522 it.advance();
523 }
524 if (needMoreContext && string.size() > prefixLength) {
525 // The last search returned the end of the buffer and asked for more context,
526 // but there is no further text. Force a search with what's available.
527 next = searchFunction(StringView(string.data(), string.size()), prefixLength, DontHaveMoreContext, needMoreContext);
528 ASSERT(!needMoreContext);
529 }
530
531 return next;
532}

534enum class NeedsContextAtParagraphStart { Yes, No };
535static VisiblePosition previousBoundary(const VisiblePosition& position, BoundarySearchFunction searchFunction,
536 NeedsContextAtParagraphStart needsContextAtParagraphStart = NeedsContextAtParagraphStart::No)
537{
538 auto boundary = position.deepEquivalent().parentEditingBoundary();
539 if (!boundary)
540 return { };
541
542 Vector<UChar, 1024> string;
543 unsigned suffixLength = 0;
544
545 auto searchRange = makeSimpleRange(makeBoundaryPointBeforeNodeContents(*boundary), position);
546 if (!searchRange)
547 return { };
548
549 if (needsContextAtParagraphStart == NeedsContextAtParagraphStart::Yes && isStartOfParagraph(position)) {
550 auto forwardsScanRange = makeSimpleRange(searchRange->start, endOfParagraph(position));
551 if (!forwardsScanRange)
552 return { };
553 for (TextIterator forwardsIterator(*forwardsScanRange); !forwardsIterator.atEnd(); forwardsIterator.advance())
554 append(string, forwardsIterator.text());
555 suffixLength = string.size();
556 } else if (requiresContextForWordBoundary(position.characterBefore())) {
557 auto forwardsScanRange = makeSimpleRange(searchRange->end, makeBoundaryPointAfterNodeContents(*boundary));
558 suffixLength = suffixLengthForRange(forwardsScanRange, string);
559 }
560
561 SimplifiedBackwardsTextIterator it(*searchRange);
562 unsigned next = backwardSearchForBoundaryWithTextIterator(it, string, suffixLength, searchFunction);
563
564 if (!next)
565 return it.atEnd() ? makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(searchRange->start) : position;
566
567 auto& node = (it.atEnd() ? *searchRange : it.range()).start.container.get();
568 if ((!suffixLength && is<Text>(node) && next <= downcast<Text>(node).length()) || (node.renderer() && node.renderer()->isBR() && !next)) {
569 // The next variable contains a usable index into a text node.
570 return makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(&node, next);
571 }
572
573 // Use the character iterator to translate the next value into a DOM position.
574 BackwardsCharacterIterator charIt(*searchRange);
575 if (next < string.size() - suffixLength)
576 charIt.advance(string.size() - suffixLength - next);
577 // FIXME: charIt can get out of shadow host.
578 return makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(charIt.range().end);
579}
580
581static VisiblePosition nextBoundary(const VisiblePosition& c, BoundarySearchFunction searchFunction)
582{
583 Position pos = c.deepEquivalent();
584 Node* boundary = pos.parentEditingBoundary();
585 if (!boundary)
586 return VisiblePosition();
587
588 Document& boundaryDocument = boundary->document();
589
590 Vector<UChar, 1024> string;
591 unsigned prefixLength = 0;
592
593 if (requiresContextForWordBoundary(c.characterAfter())) {
594 auto backwardsScanRange = makeSimpleRange(makeBoundaryPointBeforeNodeContents(boundaryDocument), c);
595 if (!backwardsScanRange)
596 return { };
597 prefixLength = prefixLengthForRange(*backwardsScanRange, string);
598 }
599
600 auto searchRange = makeSimpleRange(c, makeBoundaryPointAfterNodeContents(*boundary));
601 if (!searchRange)
602 return { };
603
604 TextIterator it(*searchRange, TextIteratorBehavior::EmitsCharactersBetweenAllVisiblePositions);
605 unsigned next = forwardSearchForBoundaryWithTextIterator(it, string, prefixLength, searchFunction);
606
607 if (it.atEnd() && next == string.size())
608 pos = makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(searchRange->end);
609 else if (next > prefixLength) {
610 // Use the character iterator to translate the next value into a DOM position.
611 CharacterIterator charIt(*searchRange, TextIteratorBehavior::EmitsCharactersBetweenAllVisiblePositions);
612 charIt.advance(next - prefixLength - 1);
613 if (charIt.atEnd())
614 return { };
615
616 auto characterRange = charIt.range();
617 pos = makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(characterRange.end);
618
619 if (charIt.text()[0] == '\n') {
620 // FIXME: workaround for collapsed range (where only start position is correct) emitted for some emitted newlines (see rdar://5192593)
621 if (VisiblePosition(pos) == VisiblePosition(makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(characterRange.start))) {
622 charIt.advance(1);
623 pos = makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(charIt.range().start);
624 }
625 }
626 }
627
628 return VisiblePosition(pos, Affinity::Upstream);
629}

633unsigned startWordBoundary(StringView text, unsigned offset, BoundarySearchContextAvailability mayHaveMoreContext, bool& needMoreContext)
634{
635 ASSERT(offset);
636 if (mayHaveMoreContext && !startOfLastWordBoundaryContext(text.substring(0, offset))) {
637 needMoreContext = true;
638 return 0;
639 }
640 needMoreContext = false;
641 int start, end;
642 U16_BACK_1(text, 0, offset);
643 findWordBoundary(text, offset, &start, &end);
644 return start;
645}
646
647VisiblePosition startOfWord(const VisiblePosition& c, EWordSide side)
648{
649 // FIXME: This returns a null VP for c at the start of the document
650 // and side == LeftWordIfOnBoundary
651 VisiblePosition p = c;
652 if (side == RightWordIfOnBoundary) {
653 // at paragraph end, the startofWord is the current position
654 if (isEndOfParagraph(c))
655 return c;
656
657 p = c.next();
658 if (p.isNull())
659 return c;
660 }
661 return previousBoundary(p, startWordBoundary);
662}
663
664unsigned endWordBoundary(StringView text, unsigned offset, BoundarySearchContextAvailability mayHaveMoreContext, bool& needMoreContext)
665{
666 ASSERT(offset <= text.length());
667 if (mayHaveMoreContext && endOfFirstWordBoundaryContext(text.substring(offset)) == text.length() - offset) {
668 needMoreContext = true;
669 return text.length();
670 }
671 needMoreContext = false;
672 int end;
673 findEndWordBoundary(text, offset, &end);
674 return end;
675}
676
677VisiblePosition endOfWord(const VisiblePosition& c, EWordSide side)
678{
679 VisiblePosition p = c;
680 if (side == LeftWordIfOnBoundary) {
681 if (isStartOfParagraph(c))
682 return c;
683
684 p = c.previous();
685 if (p.isNull())
686 return c;
687 } else if (isEndOfParagraph(c))
688 return c;
689
690 return nextBoundary(p, endWordBoundary);
691}

693static unsigned previousWordPositionBoundary(StringView text, unsigned offset, BoundarySearchContextAvailability mayHaveMoreContext, bool& needMoreContext)
694{

696 needMoreContext = true;
697 return 0;
698 }
699 needMoreContext = false;

701}

730enum LineEndpointComputationMode { UseLogicalOrdering, UseInlineBoxOrdering };
731static VisiblePosition startPositionForLine(const VisiblePosition& c, LineEndpointComputationMode mode)
732{
733 if (c.isNull())
734 return VisiblePosition();
735
736 auto line = RenderedPosition(c).line();
737 if (!line) {
738 // There are VisiblePositions at offset 0 in blocks without
739 // RootInlineBoxes, like empty editable blocks and bordered blocks.
740 Position p = c.deepEquivalent();
741 if (p.deprecatedNode()->renderer() && p.deprecatedNode()->renderer()->isRenderBlock() && !p.deprecatedEditingOffset())
742 return c;
743
744 return VisiblePosition();
745 }
746
747 Node* startNode;
748 LayoutIntegration::RunIterator startRun = mode == UseLogicalOrdering ? line.logicalStartRunWithNode() : line.firstRun();
749 // Generated content (e.g. list markers and CSS :before and :after pseudoelements) have no corresponding DOM element,
750 // and so cannot be represented by a VisiblePosition. Use whatever follows instead.
751 while (true) {
752 if (!startRun)
753 return VisiblePosition();
754
755 startNode = startRun->renderer().nonPseudoNode();
756 if (startNode)
757 break;
758
759 if (mode == UseLogicalOrdering)
760 startRun.traverseNextOnLineInLogicalOrder();
761 else
762 startRun.traverseNextOnLine();
763 }
764
765 return is<Text>(*startNode) ? Position(downcast<Text>(startNode), downcast<LayoutIntegration::PathTextRun>(*startRun).start())
766 : positionBeforeNode(startNode);
767}
768
769static VisiblePosition startOfLine(const VisiblePosition& c, LineEndpointComputationMode mode, bool* reachedBoundary)
770{
771 if (reachedBoundary)
772 *reachedBoundary = false;
773 // TODO: this is the current behavior that might need to be fixed.
774 // Please refer to https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=49107 for detail.
775 VisiblePosition visPos = startPositionForLine(c, mode);
776
777 if (mode == UseLogicalOrdering) {
778 if (Node* editableRoot = highestEditableRoot(c.deepEquivalent())) {
779 if (!editableRoot->contains(visPos.deepEquivalent().containerNode())) {
780 VisiblePosition newPosition = firstPositionInNode(editableRoot);
781 if (reachedBoundary)
782 *reachedBoundary = c == newPosition;
783 return newPosition;
784 }
785 }
786 }
787
788 return c.honorEditingBoundaryAtOrBefore(visPos, reachedBoundary);
789}

791// FIXME: Rename this function to reflect the fact it ignores bidi levels.
792VisiblePosition startOfLine(const VisiblePosition& currentPosition)
793{
794 return startOfLine(currentPosition, UseInlineBoxOrdering, nullptr);
795}
796
797VisiblePosition logicalStartOfLine(const VisiblePosition& currentPosition, bool* reachedBoundary)
798{
799 return startOfLine(currentPosition, UseLogicalOrdering, reachedBoundary);
800}
801
802static VisiblePosition endPositionForLine(const VisiblePosition& c, LineEndpointComputationMode mode)
803{
804 if (c.isNull())
805 return VisiblePosition();
806
807 auto line = RenderedPosition(c).line();
808 if (!line) {
809 // There are VisiblePositions at offset 0 in blocks without
810 // RootInlineBoxes, like empty editable blocks and bordered blocks.
811 Position p = c.deepEquivalent();
812 if (p.deprecatedNode()->renderer() && p.deprecatedNode()->renderer()->isRenderBlock() && !p.deprecatedEditingOffset())
813 return c;
814 return VisiblePosition();
815 }
816
817 Node* endNode;
818 LayoutIntegration::RunIterator endRun = mode == UseLogicalOrdering ? line.logicalEndRunWithNode() : line.lastRun();
819 // Generated content (e.g. list markers and CSS :before and :after pseudoelements) have no corresponding DOM element,
820 // and so cannot be represented by a VisiblePosition. Use whatever precedes instead.
821 while (true) {
822 if (!endRun)
823 return VisiblePosition();
824
825 endNode = endRun->renderer().nonPseudoNode();
826 if (endNode)
827 break;
828
829 if (mode == UseLogicalOrdering)
830 endRun.traversePreviousOnLineInLogicalOrder();
831 else
832 endRun.traversePreviousOnLine();
833 }
834
835 Position pos;
836 if (is<HTMLBRElement>(*endNode))
837 pos = positionBeforeNode(endNode);
838 else if (is<LayoutIntegration::PathTextRun>(*endRun) && is<Text>(*endNode)) {
839 auto& endTextRun = downcast<LayoutIntegration::PathTextRun>(*endRun);
840 int endOffset = endTextRun.start();
841 if (!endTextRun.isLineBreak())
842 endOffset += endTextRun.length();
843 pos = Position(downcast<Text>(endNode), endOffset);
844 } else
845 pos = positionAfterNode(endNode);
846
847 return VisiblePosition(pos, Affinity::Upstream);
848}

850static bool inSameLogicalLine(const VisiblePosition& a, const VisiblePosition& b)
851{
852 return a.isNotNull() && logicalStartOfLine(a) == logicalStartOfLine(b);
853}
854
855static VisiblePosition endOfLine(const VisiblePosition& c, LineEndpointComputationMode mode, bool* reachedBoundary)
856{
857 if (reachedBoundary)
858 *reachedBoundary = false;
859 // TODO: this is the current behavior that might need to be fixed.
860 // Please refer to https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=49107 for detail.
861 VisiblePosition visPos = endPositionForLine(c, mode);
862
863 if (mode == UseLogicalOrdering) {
864 // Make sure the end of line is at the same line as the given input position. For a wrapping line, the logical end
865 // position for the not-last-2-lines might incorrectly hand back the logical beginning of the next line.
866 // For example, <div contenteditable dir="rtl" style="line-break:before-white-space">abcdefg abcdefg abcdefg
867 // a abcdefg abcdefg abcdefg abcdefg abcdefg abcdefg abcdefg abcdefg abcdefg abcdefg </div>
868 // In this case, use the previous position of the computed logical end position.
869 if (!inSameLogicalLine(c, visPos))
870 visPos = visPos.previous();
871
872 if (Node* editableRoot = highestEditableRoot(c.deepEquivalent())) {
873 if (!editableRoot->contains(visPos.deepEquivalent().containerNode())) {
874 VisiblePosition newPosition = lastPositionInNode(editableRoot);
875 if (reachedBoundary)
876 *reachedBoundary = c == newPosition;
877 return newPosition;
878 }
879 }
880
881 return c.honorEditingBoundaryAtOrAfter(visPos, reachedBoundary);
882 }
883
884 // Make sure the end of line is at the same line as the given input position. Else use the previous position to
885 // obtain end of line. This condition happens when the input position is before the space character at the end
886 // of a soft-wrapped non-editable line. In this scenario, endPositionForLine would incorrectly hand back a position
887 // in the next line instead. This fix is to account for the discrepancy between lines with webkit-line-break:after-white-space style
888 // versus lines without that style, which would break before a space by default.
889 if (!inSameLine(c, visPos)) {
890 visPos = c.previous();
891 if (visPos.isNull())
892 return VisiblePosition();
893 visPos = endPositionForLine(visPos, UseInlineBoxOrdering);
894 }
895
896 return c.honorEditingBoundaryAtOrAfter(visPos, reachedBoundary);
897}

903}

905VisiblePosition logicalEndOfLine(const VisiblePosition& currentPosition, bool* reachedBoundary)

930static inline IntPoint absoluteLineDirectionPointToLocalPointInBlock(LayoutIntegration::LineIterator& line, int lineDirectionPoint)
931{
932 auto& containingBlock = line->containingBlock();
933 FloatPoint absoluteBlockPoint = containingBlock.localToAbsolute(FloatPoint()) - toFloatSize(containingBlock.scrollPosition());
934
935 if (containingBlock.isHorizontalWritingMode())
936 return IntPoint(lineDirectionPoint - absoluteBlockPoint.x(), line->blockDirectionPointInLine());
937
938 return IntPoint(line->blockDirectionPointInLine(), lineDirectionPoint - absoluteBlockPoint.y());
939}

941static Element* rootEditableOrDocumentElement(Node& node, EditableType editableType)
942{
943 if (hasEditableStyle(node, editableType))
944 return editableRootForPosition(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(&node), editableType);
945 return node.document().documentElement();

947
948VisiblePosition previousLinePosition(const VisiblePosition& visiblePosition, int lineDirectionPoint, EditableType editableType)
949{
950 Position p = visiblePosition.deepEquivalent();
951 Node* node = p.deprecatedNode();
952
953 if (!node)
954 return VisiblePosition();
955
956 node->document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
957
958 RenderObject* renderer = node->renderer();
959 if (!renderer)
960 return VisiblePosition();
961
962 LayoutIntegration::LineIterator line;
963 if (auto run = visiblePosition.inlineRunAndOffset().run) {
964 line = run.line().previous();
965 // We want to skip zero height boxes.
966 // This could happen in case it is a LegacyRootInlineBox with trailing floats.
967 if (!line || !line->logicalHeight() || !line.firstRun())
968 line = { };
969 }
970
971 if (!line) {
972 Position position = previousLineCandidatePosition(node, visiblePosition, editableType);
973 if (position.isNotNull()) {
974 RenderedPosition renderedPosition(position);
975 line = renderedPosition.line();
976 if (!line)
977 return position;
978 }
979 }
980
981 if (line) {
982 // FIXME: Can be wrong for multi-column layout and with transforms.
983 auto pointInLine = absoluteLineDirectionPointToLocalPointInBlock(line, lineDirectionPoint);
984 auto& renderer = line.closestRunForPoint(pointInLine, isEditablePosition(p))->renderer();
985 Node* node = renderer.node();
986 if (node && editingIgnoresContent(*node))
987 return positionInParentBeforeNode(node);
988 return const_cast<RenderObject&>(renderer).positionForPoint(pointInLine, nullptr);
989 }
990
991 // Could not find a previous line. This means we must already be on the first line.
992 // Move to the start of the content in this block, which effectively moves us
993 // to the start of the line we're on.
994 Element* rootElement = rootEditableOrDocumentElement(*node, editableType);
995 if (!rootElement)
996 return VisiblePosition();
997 return firstPositionInNode(rootElement);
998}
999
1000VisiblePosition nextLinePosition(const VisiblePosition& visiblePosition, int lineDirectionPoint, EditableType editableType)
1001{
1002 Position p = visiblePosition.deepEquivalent();
1003 Node* node = p.deprecatedNode();
1004 if (!node)
1005 return VisiblePosition();
1006
1007 node->document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
1008
1009 if (!node->renderer())
1010 return VisiblePosition();
1011
1012 LayoutIntegration::LineIterator line;
1013 if (auto run = visiblePosition.inlineRunAndOffset().run) {
1014 line = run.line().next();
1015 // We want to skip zero height boxes.
1016 // This could happen in case it is a LegacyRootInlineBox with trailing floats.
1017 if (!line || !line->logicalHeight() || !line.firstRun())
1018 line = { };
1019 }
1020
1021 if (!line) {
1022 // FIXME: We need do the same in previousLinePosition.
1023 Node* child = node->traverseToChildAt(p.deprecatedEditingOffset());
1024 node = child ? child : node->lastDescendant();
1025 Position position = nextLineCandidatePosition(node, visiblePosition, editableType);
1026 if (position.isNotNull()) {
1027 RenderedPosition renderedPosition(position);
1028 line = renderedPosition.line();
1029 if (!line)
1030 return position;
1031 }
1032 }
1033
1034 if (line) {
1035 // FIXME: Can be wrong for multi-column layout and with transforms.
1036 auto pointInLine = absoluteLineDirectionPointToLocalPointInBlock(line, lineDirectionPoint);
1037 auto& renderer = line.closestRunForPoint(pointInLine, isEditablePosition(p))->renderer();
1038 Node* node = renderer.node();
1039 if (node && editingIgnoresContent(*node))
1040 return positionInParentBeforeNode(node);
1041 return const_cast<RenderObject&>(renderer).positionForPoint(pointInLine, nullptr);
1042 }
1043
1044 // Could not find a next line. This means we must already be on the last line.
1045 // Move to the end of the content in this block, which effectively moves us
1046 // to the end of the line we're on.
1047 Element* rootElement = rootEditableOrDocumentElement(*node, editableType);
1048 if (!rootElement)
1049 return VisiblePosition();
1050 return lastPositionInNode(rootElement);
1051}

1101Node* findStartOfParagraph(Node* startNode, Node* highestRoot, Node* startBlock, int& offset, Position::AnchorType& type, EditingBoundaryCrossingRule boundaryCrossingRule)
1102{
1103 Node* node = startNode;
1104 Node* n = startNode;
1105 while (n) {
1106 if (boundaryCrossingRule == CannotCrossEditingBoundary && !Position::nodeIsUserSelectAll(n) && n->hasEditableStyle() != startNode->hasEditableStyle())
1107 break;
1108 if (boundaryCrossingRule == CanSkipOverEditingBoundary) {
1109 while (n && n->hasEditableStyle() != startNode->hasEditableStyle())
1110 n = NodeTraversal::previousPostOrder(*n, startBlock);
1111 if (!n || !n->isDescendantOf(highestRoot))
1112 break;
1113 }
1114 RenderObject* r = n->renderer();
1115 if (!r) {
1116 n = NodeTraversal::previousPostOrder(*n, startBlock);
1117 continue;
1118 }
1119 const RenderStyle& style = r->style();
1120 if (style.visibility() != Visibility::Visible) {
1121 n = NodeTraversal::previousPostOrder(*n, startBlock);
1122 continue;
1123 }
1124
1125 if (r->isBR() || isBlock(n))
1126 break;
1127
1128 if (is<RenderText>(*r) && downcast<RenderText>(*r).hasRenderedText()) {
1129 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(is<Text>(*n));
1130 type = Position::PositionIsOffsetInAnchor;
1131 if (style.preserveNewline()) {
1132 StringImpl& text = downcast<RenderText>(*r).text();
1133 int i = text.length();
1134 int o = offset;
1135 if (n == startNode && o < i)
1136 i = std::max(0, o);
1137 while (--i >= 0) {
1138 if (text[i] == '\n') {
1139 offset = i + 1;
1140 return n;
1141 }
1142 }
1143 }
1144 node = n;
1145 offset = 0;
1146 n = NodeTraversal::previousPostOrder(*n, startBlock);
1147 } else if (editingIgnoresContent(*n) || isRenderedTable(n)) {
1148 node = n;
1149 type = Position::PositionIsBeforeAnchor;
1150 n = n->previousSibling() ? n->previousSibling() : NodeTraversal::previousPostOrder(*n, startBlock);
1151 } else
1152 n = NodeTraversal::previousPostOrder(*n, startBlock);
1153 }
1154
1155 return node;
1156}
1157
1158Node* findEndOfParagraph(Node* startNode, Node* highestRoot, Node* stayInsideBlock, int& offset, Position::AnchorType& type, EditingBoundaryCrossingRule boundaryCrossingRule)
1159{
1160 Node* node = startNode;
1161 Node* n = startNode;
1162 while (n) {
1163 if (boundaryCrossingRule == CannotCrossEditingBoundary && !Position::nodeIsUserSelectAll(n) && n->hasEditableStyle() != startNode->hasEditableStyle())
1164 break;
1165 if (boundaryCrossingRule == CanSkipOverEditingBoundary) {
1166 while (n && n->hasEditableStyle() != startNode->hasEditableStyle())
1167 n = NodeTraversal::next(*n, stayInsideBlock);
1168 if (!n || !n->isDescendantOf(highestRoot))
1169 break;
1170 }
1171
1172 RenderObject* r = n->renderer();
1173 if (!r) {
1174 n = NodeTraversal::next(*n, stayInsideBlock);
1175 continue;
1176 }
1177 const RenderStyle& style = r->style();
1178 if (style.visibility() != Visibility::Visible) {
1179 n = NodeTraversal::next(*n, stayInsideBlock);
1180 continue;
1181 }
1182
1183 // FIXME: This is wrong when startNode is a block. We should return a position after the block.
1184 if (r->isBR() || isBlock(n))
1185 break;
1186
1187 // FIXME: We avoid returning a position where the renderer can't accept the caret.
1188 if (is<RenderText>(*r) && downcast<RenderText>(*r).hasRenderedText()) {
1189 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(is<Text>(*n));
1190 type = Position::PositionIsOffsetInAnchor;
1191 if (style.preserveNewline()) {
1192 StringImpl& text = downcast<RenderText>(*r).text();
1193 int o = n == startNode ? offset : 0;
1194 int length = text.length();
1195 for (int i = o; i < length; ++i) {
1196 if (text[i] == '\n') {
1197 offset = i;
1198 return n;
1199 }
1200 }
1201 }
1202 node = n;
1203 offset = r->caretMaxOffset();
1204 n = NodeTraversal::next(*n, stayInsideBlock);
1205 } else if (editingIgnoresContent(*n) || isRenderedTable(n)) {
1206 node = n;
1207 type = Position::PositionIsAfterAnchor;
1208 n = NodeTraversal::nextSkippingChildren(*n, stayInsideBlock);
1209 } else
1210 n = NodeTraversal::next(*n, stayInsideBlock);
1211 }
1212 return node;
1213}
1214
1215VisiblePosition startOfParagraph(const VisiblePosition& c, EditingBoundaryCrossingRule boundaryCrossingRule)
1216{
1217 Position p = c.deepEquivalent();
1218 auto* startNode = p.deprecatedNode();
1219
1220 if (!startNode)
1221 return VisiblePosition();
1222
1223 if (isRenderedAsNonInlineTableImageOrHR(startNode))
1224 return positionBeforeNode(startNode);
1225
1226 Node* startBlock = enclosingBlock(startNode);
1227
1228 auto* highestRoot = highestEditableRoot(p);
1229 int offset = p.deprecatedEditingOffset();
1230 Position::AnchorType type = p.anchorType();
1231
1232 auto* node = findStartOfParagraph(startNode, highestRoot, startBlock, offset, type, boundaryCrossingRule);
1233
1234 if (is<Text>(node))
1235 return Position(downcast<Text>(node), offset);
1236
1237 if (type == Position::PositionIsOffsetInAnchor) {
1238 ASSERT(type == Position::PositionIsOffsetInAnchor || !offset);
1239 return Position(node, offset, type);
1240 }
1241
1242 return Position(node, type);
1243}
1244
1245VisiblePosition endOfParagraph(const VisiblePosition& c, EditingBoundaryCrossingRule boundaryCrossingRule)
1246{
1247 if (c.isNull())
1248 return VisiblePosition();
1249
1250 Position p = c.deepEquivalent();
1251 auto* startNode = p.deprecatedNode();
1252
1253 if (isRenderedAsNonInlineTableImageOrHR(startNode))
1254 return positionAfterNode(startNode);
1255
1256 auto* startBlock = enclosingBlock(startNode);
1257 auto* stayInsideBlock = startBlock;
1258
1259 auto* highestRoot = highestEditableRoot(p);
1260 int offset = p.deprecatedEditingOffset();
1261 Position::AnchorType type = p.anchorType();
1262
1263 auto* node = findEndOfParagraph(startNode, highestRoot, stayInsideBlock, offset, type, boundaryCrossingRule);
1264
1265 if (is<Text>(node))
1266 return Position(downcast<Text>(node), offset);
1267
1268 if (type == Position::PositionIsOffsetInAnchor)
1269 return Position(node, offset, type);
1270
1271 return Position(node, type);
1272}

1277 VisiblePosition paragraphEnd(endOfParagraph(visiblePosition, CanSkipOverEditingBoundary));
1278 VisiblePosition afterParagraphEnd(paragraphEnd.next(CannotCrossEditingBoundary));

1280 // is not the start of the next paragraph.
1281 if (isFirstPositionAfterTable(afterParagraphEnd))
1282 return afterParagraphEnd.next(CannotCrossEditingBoundary);
1283 return afterParagraphEnd;
1284}

1331
1332VisiblePosition startOfBlock(const VisiblePosition& visiblePosition, EditingBoundaryCrossingRule rule)
1333{
1334 Position position = visiblePosition.deepEquivalent();
1335 Node* startBlock;
1336 if (!position.containerNode() || !(startBlock = enclosingBlock(position.containerNode(), rule)))
1337 return VisiblePosition();
1338 return firstPositionInNode(startBlock);
1339}

1348}

1353}

1366
1367VisiblePosition startOfDocument(const Node* node)
1368{
1369 if (!node || !node->document().documentElement())
1370 return VisiblePosition();
1371
1372 // The canonicalization of the position at (documentElement, 0) can turn the visible
1373 // position to null, even when there's a valid candidate to be had, because the root HTML element
1374 // is not content editable. So we construct directly from the valid candidate.
1375 Position firstCandidate = nextCandidate(makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(node->document().documentElement(), 0));
1376 if (firstCandidate.isNull())
1377 return VisiblePosition();
1378 return VisiblePosition(firstCandidate);
1379}

1382{
1383 return startOfDocument(c.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode());
1384}
1385
1386VisiblePosition endOfDocument(const Node* node)
1387{
1388 if (!node || !node->document().documentElement())
1389 return VisiblePosition();
1390
1391 // (As above, in startOfDocument.) The canonicalization can reject valid visible positions
1392 // when descending from the root element, so we construct the visible position directly from a
1393 // valid candidate.
1394 Position lastPosition = makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(node->document().documentElement(), node->document().documentElement()->countChildNodes());
1395 Position lastCandidate = previousCandidate(lastPosition);
1396 if (lastCandidate.isNull())
1397 return VisiblePosition();
1398 return VisiblePosition(lastCandidate);
1399}
1400
1401VisiblePosition endOfDocument(const VisiblePosition& c)
1402{
1403 return endOfDocument(c.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode());
1404}

1406bool inSameDocument(const VisiblePosition& a, const VisiblePosition& b)
1407{

1410 if (!an)
1411 return false;
1412 Position bp = b.deepEquivalent();
1413 Node* bn = bp.deprecatedNode();

1415 return true;
1416
1417 return &an->document() == &bn->document();

1465static bool directionIsDownstream(SelectionDirection direction)
1466{
1467 if (direction == SelectionDirection::Backward)
1468 return false;
1469 if (direction == SelectionDirection::Forward)
1470 return true;
1471
1472 // FIXME: this code doesn't take into account the original direction of the element.
1473 // I'm not fixing this now because I'm afraid there is some code in UIKit relying on
1474 // this wrong behavior.
1475 return direction == SelectionDirection::Right;
1476}
1477
1478bool atBoundaryOfGranularity(const VisiblePosition& vp, TextGranularity granularity, SelectionDirection direction)
1479{
1480 if (granularity == TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity)
1481 return true;
1482
1483 VisiblePosition boundary;
1484
1485 bool useDownstream = directionIsDownstream(direction);
1486
1487 switch (granularity) {
1488 case TextGranularity::WordGranularity:
1489 // visible_units claims erroneously that the start and the end
1490 // of a paragraph are the end and start of a word, respectively.
1491 if ((useDownstream && isStartOfParagraph(vp)) || (!useDownstream && isEndOfParagraph(vp)))
1492 return false;
1493
1494 // Note that "Left" and "Right" in this context apparently mean "upstream/previous" and "downstream/next".
1495 boundary = useDownstream ? endOfWord(vp, LeftWordIfOnBoundary) : startOfWord(vp, RightWordIfOnBoundary);
1496 break;
1497
1498 case TextGranularity::SentenceGranularity:
1499 boundary = useDownstream ? endOfSentence(previousSentencePosition(vp)) : startOfSentence(nextSentencePosition(vp));
1500 break;
1501
1502 case TextGranularity::LineGranularity:
1503 boundary = vp;
1504 boundary.setAffinity(useDownstream ? Affinity::Upstream : Affinity::Downstream);
1505 boundary = useDownstream ? endOfLine(boundary) : startOfLine(boundary);
1506 break;
1507
1508 case TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity:
1509 boundary = useDownstream ? endOfParagraph(vp) : startOfParagraph(vp);
1510 break;
1511
1512 case TextGranularity::DocumentGranularity:
1513 boundary = useDownstream ? endOfDocument(vp) : startOfDocument(vp);
1514 break;
1515
1516 default:
1517 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1518 break;
1519 }
1520
1521 return vp == boundary;
1522}
1523
1524bool withinTextUnitOfGranularity(const VisiblePosition& vp, TextGranularity granularity, SelectionDirection direction)
1525{
1526 if (granularity == TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity || granularity == TextGranularity::DocumentGranularity)
1527 return true;
1528
1529 bool useDownstream = directionIsDownstream(direction);
1530
1531 VisiblePosition prevBoundary;
1532 VisiblePosition nextBoundary;
1533
1534 switch (granularity) {
1535 case TextGranularity::WordGranularity:
1536 // Note that "Left" and "Right" in this context apparently mean "upstream/previous" and "downstream/next".
1537 prevBoundary = startOfWord(vp, (useDownstream ? RightWordIfOnBoundary : LeftWordIfOnBoundary));
1538 nextBoundary = endOfWord(vp, (useDownstream ? RightWordIfOnBoundary : LeftWordIfOnBoundary));
1539
1540 // Workaround for <rdar://problem/7259611> Word boundary code on iPhone gives different results than desktop
1541 if (endOfWord(prevBoundary, RightWordIfOnBoundary) != nextBoundary)
1542 return false;
1543
1544 break;
1545
1546 case TextGranularity::SentenceGranularity:
1547 prevBoundary = startOfSentence(vp);
1548 nextBoundary = endOfSentence(vp);
1549 break;
1550
1551 case TextGranularity::LineGranularity:
1552 prevBoundary = startOfLine(vp);
1553 nextBoundary = endOfLine(vp);
1554
1555 if (prevBoundary == nextBoundary) {
1556 nextBoundary = nextLinePosition(nextBoundary, 0);
1557 nextBoundary.setAffinity(Affinity::Upstream);
1558 if (!inSameLine(prevBoundary, nextBoundary))
1559 nextBoundary = vp.next();
1560 }
1561 break;
1562
1563 case TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity:
1564 prevBoundary = startOfParagraph(vp);
1565 nextBoundary = endOfParagraph(vp);
1566 break;
1567
1568 default:
1569 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1570 break;
1571 }
1572
1573 if (prevBoundary == nextBoundary)
1574 return false;
1575
1576 if (vp == prevBoundary)
1577 return useDownstream;
1578
1579 if (vp == nextBoundary)
1580 return !useDownstream;
1581
1582 return (prevBoundary < vp && vp < nextBoundary);
1583}
1584
1585static VisiblePosition nextCharacterBoundaryInDirection(const VisiblePosition& vp, SelectionDirection direction, EditingBoundaryCrossingRule rule)
1586{
1587 return directionIsDownstream(direction) ? vp.next(rule) : vp.previous(rule);
1588}
1589
1590static VisiblePosition nextWordBoundaryInDirection(const VisiblePosition& vp, SelectionDirection direction)
1591{
1592 bool useDownstream = directionIsDownstream(direction);
1593 bool withinUnitOfGranularity = withinTextUnitOfGranularity(vp, TextGranularity::WordGranularity, direction);
1594 VisiblePosition result;
1595
1596 if (useDownstream) {
1597 if (withinUnitOfGranularity)
1598 result = endOfWord(vp, RightWordIfOnBoundary);
1599 else {
1600 VisiblePosition start = startOfWord(vp, RightWordIfOnBoundary);
1601 if (start > vp && start != endOfWord(start))
1602 result = start;
1603 else {
1604 // Do same thing as backwards traveling below.
1605 start = vp;
1606 while (true) {
1607 result = startOfWord(nextWordPosition(start), RightWordIfOnBoundary);
1608
1609 if (result == start)
1610 break;
1611
1612 // We failed to find a word boundary.
1613 if (result.isNull() || result < start)
1614 return VisiblePosition();
1615
1616 // We consider successs also the case where start is before element and result is after.
1617 // This covers moving past images like words.
1618 if (result != endOfWord(result)
1619 || (result.deepEquivalent().anchorNode() == start.deepEquivalent().anchorNode()
1620 && result.deepEquivalent().anchorType() == Position::PositionIsAfterAnchor
1621 && start.deepEquivalent().anchorType() == Position::PositionIsBeforeAnchor))
1622 break;
1623
1624 start = result;
1625 }
1626 }
1627 }
1628 } else {
1629 if (withinUnitOfGranularity)
1630 result = startOfWord(vp, LeftWordIfOnBoundary);
1631 else {
1632 // This is complicated because:
1633 // When given "Blah blah.|", endOfWord is "Blah blah|.", and previousWordPosition is "Blah| blah."
1634 // When given "Blah blah. |", endOfWord is "Blah blah.| ", and previousWordPosition is "Blah |blah. ".
1635 VisiblePosition end = endOfWord(vp, LeftWordIfOnBoundary);
1636 if (end < vp && end != startOfWord(end))
1637 result = end;
1638 else {
1639 end = vp;
1640 while (true) {
1641 result = endOfWord(previousWordPosition(end), RightWordIfOnBoundary);
1642
1643 if (result == end)
1644 break;
1645
1646 if (result.isNull() || result > end)
1647 return VisiblePosition();
1648
1649 if (result != startOfWord(result))
1650 break;
1651
1652 end = result;
1653 }
1654 }
1655 }
1656 }
1657
1658 if (result == vp)
1659 return VisiblePosition();
1660
1661 return result;
1662}
1663
1664static VisiblePosition nextSentenceBoundaryInDirection(const VisiblePosition& vp, SelectionDirection direction)
1665{
1666 bool useDownstream = directionIsDownstream(direction);
1667 bool withinUnitOfGranularity = withinTextUnitOfGranularity(vp, TextGranularity::SentenceGranularity, direction);
1668 VisiblePosition result;
1669
1670 if (withinUnitOfGranularity)
1671 result = useDownstream ? endOfSentence(vp) : startOfSentence(vp);
1672 else {
1673 result = useDownstream ? nextSentencePosition(vp) : previousSentencePosition(vp);
1674 if (result.isNull() || result == vp)
1675 return VisiblePosition();
1676
1677 result = useDownstream ? startOfSentence(vp) : endOfSentence(vp);
1678 }
1679
1680 if (result == vp)
1681 return VisiblePosition();
1682
1683 // Positions can only be compared if they are in the same tree scope.
1684 ASSERT_IMPLIES(areVisiblePositionsInSameTreeScope(result, vp), useDownstream ? (result > vp) : (result < vp));
1685
1686 return result;
1687}

1689static VisiblePosition nextLineBoundaryInDirection(const VisiblePosition& vp, SelectionDirection direction)
1690{
1691 bool useDownstream = directionIsDownstream(direction);
1692 VisiblePosition result = vp;
1693
1694 if (useDownstream) {
1695 result.setAffinity(Affinity::Downstream);
1696 result = isEndOfLine(result) ? startOfLine(nextLinePosition(result, result.lineDirectionPointForBlockDirectionNavigation())) : endOfLine(result);
1697 } else {
1698 result.setAffinity(Affinity::Upstream);
1699 result = isStartOfLine(result) ? endOfLine(previousLinePosition(result, result.lineDirectionPointForBlockDirectionNavigation())) : startOfLine(result);
1700 }
1701
1702 return result;
1703}

1705static VisiblePosition nextParagraphBoundaryInDirection(const VisiblePosition& position, SelectionDirection direction)
1706{
1707 auto useDownstream = directionIsDownstream(direction);
1708 auto lineDirection = position.lineDirectionPointForBlockDirectionNavigation();
1709 if (atBoundaryOfGranularity(position, TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity, direction))
1710 return useDownstream ? startOfParagraph(nextParagraphPosition(position, lineDirection)) : endOfParagraph(previousParagraphPosition(position, lineDirection));
1711 ASSERT(withinTextUnitOfGranularity(position, TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity, direction));
1712 return useDownstream ? endOfParagraph(position) : startOfParagraph(position);
1713}

1715static VisiblePosition nextDocumentBoundaryInDirection(const VisiblePosition& vp, SelectionDirection direction)
1716{
1717 return directionIsDownstream(direction) ? endOfDocument(vp) : startOfDocument(vp);
1718}

1720VisiblePosition positionOfNextBoundaryOfGranularity(const VisiblePosition& vp, TextGranularity granularity, SelectionDirection direction)
1721{
1722 switch (granularity) {
1723 case TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity:
1724 return nextCharacterBoundaryInDirection(vp, direction, CanCrossEditingBoundary);
1725 case TextGranularity::WordGranularity:
1726 return nextWordBoundaryInDirection(vp, direction);
1727 case TextGranularity::SentenceGranularity:
1728 return nextSentenceBoundaryInDirection(vp, direction);
1729 case TextGranularity::LineGranularity:
1730 return nextLineBoundaryInDirection(vp, direction);
1731 case TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity:
1732 return nextParagraphBoundaryInDirection(vp, direction);
1733 case TextGranularity::DocumentGranularity:
1734 return nextDocumentBoundaryInDirection(vp, direction);
1735 default:
1736 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1737 return VisiblePosition();
1738 }

1741std::optional<SimpleRange> enclosingTextUnitOfGranularity(const VisiblePosition& vp, TextGranularity granularity, SelectionDirection direction)
1742{
1743 // This is particularly inefficient. We could easily obtain the answer with the boundaries computed below.
1744 if (!withinTextUnitOfGranularity(vp, granularity, direction))
1745 return std::nullopt;
1746
1747 VisiblePosition prevBoundary;
1748 VisiblePosition nextBoundary;
1749 bool useDownstream = directionIsDownstream(direction);
1750
1751 switch (granularity) {
1752 case TextGranularity::CharacterGranularity:
1753 prevBoundary = vp;
1754 nextBoundary = prevBoundary.next();
1755 break;
1756
1757 case TextGranularity::WordGranularity:
1758 // NB: "Left" and "Right" in this context apparently mean "upstream/previous" and "downstream/next".
1759 if (useDownstream) {
1760 prevBoundary = startOfWord(vp, RightWordIfOnBoundary);
1761 nextBoundary = endOfWord(vp, RightWordIfOnBoundary);
1762 } else {
1763 prevBoundary = startOfWord(vp, LeftWordIfOnBoundary);
1764 nextBoundary = endOfWord(vp, LeftWordIfOnBoundary);
1765 }
1766 break;
1767
1768 case TextGranularity::SentenceGranularity:
1769 prevBoundary = startOfSentence(vp);
1770 nextBoundary = endOfSentence(vp);
1771 break;
1772
1773 case TextGranularity::LineGranularity:
1774 prevBoundary = startOfLine(vp);
1775 nextBoundary = endOfLine(vp);
1776
1777 if (prevBoundary == nextBoundary) {
1778 nextBoundary = nextLinePosition(nextBoundary, 0);
1779 nextBoundary.setAffinity(Affinity::Upstream);
1780 if (!inSameLine(prevBoundary, nextBoundary))
1781 nextBoundary = vp.next();
1782 }
1783 break;
1784
1785 case TextGranularity::ParagraphGranularity:
1786 prevBoundary = startOfParagraph(vp);
1787 nextBoundary = endOfParagraph(vp);
1788 break;
1789
1790 case TextGranularity::DocumentGranularity:
1791 prevBoundary = startOfDocument(vp);
1792 nextBoundary = endOfDocument(vp);
1793 break;
1794
1795 default:
1796 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1797 return std::nullopt;
1798 }
1799
1800 if (prevBoundary.isNull() || nextBoundary.isNull())
1801 return std::nullopt;
1802
1803 if (vp < prevBoundary || vp > nextBoundary)
1804 return std::nullopt;
1805
1806 return makeSimpleRange(prevBoundary, nextBoundary);
1807}

1809std::ptrdiff_t distanceBetweenPositions(const VisiblePosition& a, const VisiblePosition& b)
1810{
1811 if (a.isNull() || b.isNull())
1812 return 0;
1813 return a < b ? -characterCount(*makeSimpleRange(a, b)) : characterCount(*makeSimpleRange(b, a));
1814}

1816void charactersAroundPosition(const VisiblePosition& position, UChar32& oneAfter, UChar32& oneBefore, UChar32& twoBefore)
1817{
1818 const int maxCharacters = 3;
1819 UChar32 characters[maxCharacters] = { 0 };
1820
1821 if (position.isNull() || isStartOfDocument(position))
1822 return;
1823
1824 VisiblePosition startPosition = position;
1825 VisiblePosition endPosition = position;
1826
1827 VisiblePosition nextPosition = nextCharacterBoundaryInDirection(position, SelectionDirection::Forward, CannotCrossEditingBoundary);
1828 if (nextPosition.isNotNull())
1829 endPosition = nextPosition;
1830
1831 VisiblePosition previousPosition = nextCharacterBoundaryInDirection(position, SelectionDirection::Backward, CannotCrossEditingBoundary);
1832 if (previousPosition.isNotNull()) {
1833 startPosition = previousPosition;
1834 previousPosition = nextCharacterBoundaryInDirection(previousPosition, SelectionDirection::Backward, CannotCrossEditingBoundary);
1835 if (previousPosition.isNotNull())
1836 startPosition = previousPosition;
1837 }
1838
1839 if (startPosition != endPosition) {
1840 String characterString = plainText(*makeSimpleRange(startPosition, endPosition)).replace(noBreakSpace, ' ');
1841 for (int i = characterString.length() - 1, index = 0; i >= 0 && index < maxCharacters; --i) {
1842 if (!index && nextPosition.isNull())
1843 index++;
1844 characters[index++] = characterString[i];
1845 }
1846 }
1847 oneAfter = characters[0];
1848 oneBefore = characters[1];
1849 twoBefore = characters[2];
1850}

1852std::optional<SimpleRange> wordRangeFromPosition(const VisiblePosition& position)
1853{
1854 if (position.isNull())
1855 return std::nullopt;
1856
1857 if (auto range = enclosingTextUnitOfGranularity(position, TextGranularity::WordGranularity, SelectionDirection::Backward))
1858 return range;
1859 if (auto range = enclosingTextUnitOfGranularity(position, TextGranularity::WordGranularity, SelectionDirection::Forward))
1860 return range;
1861
1862 VisiblePosition currentPosition = position;
1863 do {
1864 currentPosition = positionOfNextBoundaryOfGranularity(currentPosition, TextGranularity::WordGranularity, SelectionDirection::Backward);
1865 } while (currentPosition.isNotNull() && !atBoundaryOfGranularity(currentPosition, TextGranularity::WordGranularity, SelectionDirection::Backward));
1866 if (currentPosition.isNull())
1867 currentPosition = positionOfNextBoundaryOfGranularity(position, TextGranularity::WordGranularity, SelectionDirection::Forward);
1868 return makeSimpleRange(currentPosition, position);
1869}
1870
1871VisiblePosition closestWordBoundaryForPosition(const VisiblePosition& position)
1872{
1873 VisiblePosition result;
1874 if (atBoundaryOfGranularity(position, TextGranularity::LineGranularity, SelectionDirection::Forward)) {
1875 // Don't cross line boundaries.
1876 result = position;
1877 } else if (withinTextUnitOfGranularity(position, TextGranularity::WordGranularity, SelectionDirection::Forward)) {
1878 // The position lies within a word.
1879 if (auto wordRange = enclosingTextUnitOfGranularity(position, TextGranularity::WordGranularity, SelectionDirection::Forward)) {
1880 result = makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(wordRange->start);
1881 if (distanceBetweenPositions(position, result) > 1)
1882 result = makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(wordRange->end);
1883 }
1884 } else if (atBoundaryOfGranularity(position, TextGranularity::WordGranularity, SelectionDirection::Backward)) {
1885 // The position is at the end of a word.
1886 result = position;
1887 } else {
1888 // The position is not within a word.
1889 // Go to the next boundary.
1890 result = positionOfNextBoundaryOfGranularity(position, TextGranularity::WordGranularity, SelectionDirection::Forward);
1891
1892 // If there is no such boundary we go to the end of the element.
1893 if (result.isNull())
1894 result = endOfEditableContent(position);
1895 }
1896 return result;
1897}

1899std::optional<SimpleRange> rangeExpandedByCharactersInDirectionAtWordBoundary(const VisiblePosition& position, int numberOfCharactersToExpand, SelectionDirection direction)
1900{
1901 Position start = position.deepEquivalent();
1902 Position end = position.deepEquivalent();
1903 for (int i = 0; i < numberOfCharactersToExpand; ++i) {
1904 if (direction == SelectionDirection::Backward)
1905 start = start.previous(Character);
1906 else
1907 end = end.next(Character);
1908 }
1909
1910 if (direction == SelectionDirection::Backward && !atBoundaryOfGranularity(start, TextGranularity::WordGranularity, SelectionDirection::Backward))
1911 start = startOfWord(start).deepEquivalent();
1912 if (direction == SelectionDirection::Forward && !atBoundaryOfGranularity(end, TextGranularity::WordGranularity, SelectionDirection::Forward))
1913 end = endOfWord(end).deepEquivalent();
1914
1915 return makeSimpleRange(start, end);
1916}

1918std::optional<SimpleRange> rangeExpandedAroundPositionByCharacters(const VisiblePosition& position, int numberOfCharactersToExpand)
1919{
1920 Position start = position.deepEquivalent();
1921 Position end = position.deepEquivalent();
1922 for (int i = 0; i < numberOfCharactersToExpand; ++i) {
1923 start = start.previous(Character);
1924 end = end.next(Character);
1925 }
1926 return makeSimpleRange(start, end);
1927}
1928
1929std::pair<VisiblePosition, WithinWordBoundary> wordBoundaryForPositionWithoutCrossingLine(const VisiblePosition& position)
1930{
1931 if (atBoundaryOfGranularity(position, TextGranularity::LineGranularity, SelectionDirection::Forward))
1932 return { position, WithinWordBoundary::No };
1933
1934 if (withinTextUnitOfGranularity(position, TextGranularity::WordGranularity, SelectionDirection::Forward)) {
1935 auto adjustedPosition = position;
1936 if (auto wordRange = enclosingTextUnitOfGranularity(position, TextGranularity::WordGranularity, SelectionDirection::Forward)) {
1937 adjustedPosition = makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(wordRange->start);
1938 if (distanceBetweenPositions(position, adjustedPosition) > 1)
1939 adjustedPosition = makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(wordRange->end);
1940 }
1941 return { adjustedPosition, WithinWordBoundary::Yes };
1942 }
1943
1944 if (atBoundaryOfGranularity(position, TextGranularity::WordGranularity, SelectionDirection::Backward))
1945 return { position, WithinWordBoundary::No };
1946
1947 auto nextWordBoundary = positionOfNextBoundaryOfGranularity(position, TextGranularity::WordGranularity, SelectionDirection::Forward);
1948 return { nextWordBoundary.isNotNull() ? nextWordBoundary : endOfEditableContent(position), WithinWordBoundary::No };
1949}
